Commentary.Commentary: The New Zealand openers, Tom Latham and Tom Blundell will open the batting for New Zealand. The Indian players are out in the middle. Jasprit Bumrah will start the proceedings.
So, 242 on the board. A decent total one would feel if the Indian bowlers can striker early in this final session. Let's see how it pans out once the Kiwi openers come out to face the Indians.

Kyle Jamieson is down for a quick chat. He says that it is a special feeling to get to a 5-fer in front of the home crowd. Hagley Oval he mentions is very special as he has played a lot of cricket here. Further says that like Wellington the pitch has something for the fast bowlers and they are pretty satisfied with restricting India to 240 odd runs.

Earlier in the game, after being asked to bat, Indians did not start well but Shaw raked up an aggressive half ton and scored runs briskly. After his wicket, India lost the way and lost quick wickets before Pujara and Vihari crawled India back into the game with a 81-run stand. Apart from the three mentioned, who all got to their respective half tons, none of the Indian batters left any mark with the bat.

If it was Southee in the second session, Jamieson took the onus upon himself in this one as he ripped apart the Indian batting. He ended up with a fifer, his first in Tests to force the collapse. Boult removed Shami with a ripper to close the innings.

Wow! That was some collapse from the Indians. Vihari went just before the Tea. Pujara walked in with a new partner in Pant but it was all about wickets falling in quick succession as the session started. They lost 5 wickets for 45 runs in this session with 26 of those coming between Bumrah and Shami. Pant and Jadeja who had the responsibility of taking India towards a good total after a very good stand between Pujara and Vihari but they failed to do anything of note.

OUT! TIMBER! Boult finishes the innings with a ripper! Shami was probably thinking another bouncer but Boult dishes out a fuller and inswinging one. He tries to keep it out but is late in bringing his bat down. The ball goes behind and sends the off pole for a walk. INDIA ARE BOWLED OUT FOR 242.
The Physio walks out to the middle for the necessary concussion tests. He is looking fine though. And we are ready to go now.

Ouch! Shami is hit on the helmet. He takes it off and checks. Tells Boult that he is fine. Shami backs away for another slog but the bowler follows him. He tries to pull but misses to get hit on the helmet.

SIX! Back to back sixes now and Shami and Bumrah are adding valuable runs for India. Boult bowls one in the arc of Shami. He swings hard, connects and sends it sailing over wide long on for another maximum.
SIX! Connects this time and it goes all the way. Slightly short and around off, Shami hammers it over deep mid-wicket for a biggie. That wasn't from the middle of the bat and goes over the ropes.
Bouncer on middle, this time it is Shami who tries to send it over the fence but fails to connect.
Length ball on middle, Bumrah goes for the slog again but the ball hits the inner half and goes towards square leg. They cross for a quick single.
Three more off the final ball. 9 from the over. Full and outside off, Bumrah squeezes it through gully and the batters run three.
Outside off, left alone.
Bouncer just outside off, Bumrah sways away from it.
A couple now as he pulls this short ball on middle down to deep mid-wicket. The fielder from the ring chases it down.
FOUR! He finally connects one and bags an important boundary. Length ball on middle, Bumrah flicks it past the leaping mid-wicket fielder and into the fence in the deep.
Swing and a miss again from Bumrah. A length ball just outside off, he goes for a mighty heave on the leg side but misses once again.
Full and outside off, Shami squeezes it towards gully.
Full and outside off, Shami looks to squeeze this one out but the ball hits the bottom part of the bat and then his hands. It rolls towards the off side.
Length ball on middle and leg, Shami looks to flick it to the leg side only to miss it and get hit high on the pads.
EDGY FOUR! Valuable runs! Length ball outside off, Shami goes to drive with hard hands but the ball takes a thick inside edge and races away to the fine leg fence.
Good length on off, pushed towards cover-point.
Fullish and around off, Shami drives it to covers.
And again! A length ball outside off, Bumrah throws his willow at it once again, only to miss out as the ball shapes away. Another wicket maiden from Jamieson.
Swing and a miss! Short one outside off, Bumrah throws his bat at it but makes no connection.
Beaten this time! Jamieson bowls this slightly short and just outside off. Bumrah comes forward and looks to force it towards the off side but misses.
Good length ball around off, Bumrah keeps it out.
Jasprit Bumrah is the last man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! First fifer for Jamieson in Tests and Jadeja perishes in search of quick runs! Jamieson is pumped up. Short ball on the body, Jadeja goes for the pull but ends up hitting it straight to fine leg off the top edge. Boult there dives forward and pouches the ball inches above the turf.
Shortish and around middle and leg, Jadeja keeps it out off his back foot.

Beaten! A length ball around off, it comes in with the angle as Shami tries to defend. He though is late in doing so as the ball sneaks through the gap between the bat and the pad. It goes over the stumps to the keeper.
Short and on middle, Jadeja plays a controlled pull towards deep square leg for a run. 1 ball for Shami to survive.
Now makes a leave to this length ball outside off.

FOUR! Clipped nicely! Jadeja is getting these important runs for India now. Boult sprays on the pads of Jadeja. All he needs to do is guide it to the fine leg fence. He does that nicely to bag consecutive boundaries.
FOUR! Hammered! Length ball around off, Jadeja comes down the track and lofts it over mid on for a boundary. Excellent shot and he will now look to score as many as he can.
Good length ball on middle, Jadeja keeps it out.
Mohammed Shami walks in to bat now.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another one bites the dust and India are tumbling once again. Slightly shorter ball outside off, Yadav is not one of those who will try to leave balls like these. He pokes at the ball but ends up getting a faint outside edge. The ball goes straight to the keeper and Watling will not miss out this one. A comfortable catch for him. 2nd wicket in the over and 4th in this innings for Jamieson.
Short and outside off, Yadav throws kitchen sink at it but fails to connect.
Good length ball around off, Yadav keeps it out.
Good length ball just outside off, Yadav thinks to push first but takes his bat away at the last moment.

OUT! Dragged on! Another failure for Pant. He was looking itchy out in the middle, got a couple of chances in the last over but bottles it once again. It is a length ball outside off, Pant goes for the drive away from his body. The ball takes an inside edge and hits the stumps.
Full and around off, pushed towards mid off.
Short and on middle, Pant pulls it to fine leg for a run. End of an eventful over from Boult.
FOUR! Flicked with authority! Full and on middle, Pant whips it powerfully through mid-wicket for a boundary.

EDGY FOUR! Another reprieve! Shortish and around off, Pant hops and tries to defend but the ball takes a thick outside edge and flies between the keeper and the first slip fielder and into the third man fence.

Dropped? Yes, de Grandhomme is the man. A length ball on middle, Pant looks to flick but the ball hits the upper part of his willow and goes towards de Grandhomme at mid-wicket. He lunges forward to pouch but the ball hits his fingers and does not stick. That can be a costly drop, if Pant can whack a few and take India towards 250 or more.

Another full ball on off and middle, Jadeja flicks again, finds square leg again.
On the pads of Jadeja now, he flicks but finds square leg.
On the pads, Pant clips it  behind square leg for a single.

He though this time goes for the pull. The ball takes the top edge and goes way in the air towards short fine leg. Watling calls for the catch, settles under it and gobbles it comfortably. A fighting innings from Pujara but he will be kicking himself for the way that he departs.

The Kiwi players are near the boundary ropes. The hosts now get into the huddle before they disperse to their positions out in the middle. Pujara has Rishabh Pant for the company to start post the Tea break. Wagner will finish the over in which he got rid of Vihari. Pant to face. Here we go...
... Day 1, Session 3 ...

Let's see what approach Pujara opts in the final session. Will Pant try to play his natural game or will he will try to rake up a partnership with Pujara? Or will Southee be able to take a fifer to bundle the Indians out. We will soon find out. Join us in a while for the last session.

Southee was once again brilliant with the ball, striking twice. Jamieson would feel that he was unlucky when Watling spilled an easy chance and gave a life to Vihari. Wagner kept bowling the shortish length and managed to remove Vihari just before Tea. They will now try to get a couple early and aim at the lower order of the Indian batting.

Southee once again removed the Indian skipper to begin the session on a high for the hosts. Rahane did not last long as he fell too to Southee. However, Pujara kept his end intact and then he got an able support from Vihari. The duo added 81 runs in 129 balls to take India close to 200. It will be interesting to see the approach of the Indian batters when they return for the final session.

Just at the stroke of the Tea, Vihari makes a mistake. He was going after the short balls and was scoring runs too but falls in the process. The way Indians were scoring runs, it looked like they will be able to win the session, even after losing a couple of big wickets in the form of Kohli and Rahane but this wicket means that the session is shared once again.

OUT! CAUGHT! A wicket right at the stoke of Tea. Wagner has the last laugh here. He keeps persisting with his short ball ploy and he reaps the reward for it. Once again Wagner bowls it short and on middle, Vihari shuffles across and looks to take on Wagner for the umpteenth time but he fails to get it off the middle of the bat. The ball takes the glove and goes towards the keeper where BJ Watling gobbles it and appeals and the umpire gives it out. Vihari departs after a promising knock and a good stand is broken. That will be TEA ON DAY 1!

We are back for the second session. The New Zealand players are out in the middle. Cheteshwar Pujara and Virat Kohli will resume their innings. Trent Boult will start the proceedings after Lunch.
... Day 1, Session 2 ...

So, after the Lunch break, India will look to keep on getting the runs with minimal damage while the Kiwis would look to pick up wickets as quickly as possible. The session after Lunch promises to be another promising one. Join us for that at 1440 Local.

New Zealand, on the other hand, were not poor with the ball. They bowled tight lines and lengths and troubled the batters a bit but Prithvi Shaw played some delightful shots to their bowling. Boult has been impressive while Colin de Grandhomme was good in his opening spell. Kyle Jamieson was the other bowler to get into the wickets column as he picked up the wicket of Shaw. Tom Latham has to be credited for his wicket as he took a brilliant catch to send the half-centurion packing. Overall, the Kiwis will be happy with the session.

23 overs, 85 runs and two wickets. India have done a much better job with the bat so far than they did in the First Test. They would have been happier if they had not lost the wicket of Prithvi Shaw in the later half of the session. They started positively in this session with Shaw going all guns blazing at the start. Mayank Agarwal lost his wicket to Boult but then Shaw and Pujara stitched a good 50-run stand before Shaw was out to a brilliant catch from Tom Latham. Pujara has been defensive and has been joined by the Indian skipper, Virat Kohli who has looked good so far.

Neil Wagner is now down for an interview who became a father recently. He says that it has been a pretty special week and it is nice to be back with the guys and play some Test cricket. Adds that he and his wife were watching the first game from the hospital and it was good to see the boys playing well. Goes onto say that he is looking forward to this game.

Ajinkya Rahane is down for an interview. He says that they were expecting it to rain today but it is good to see that it has cleared now. Adds that they are looking forward to this game. States that they got starts in Wellington and it is important that they get partnerships. Goes onto say that this wicket plays really well and there is more bounce on this wicket. States that they need to adjust to the conditions quickly.

Pitch report - Mark Richardson says that there is a lot of grass on this wicket.  Says that it will remain green for a long period of time. Adds that it is a spongy wicket with some moisture on it and it might take two days to harden up. Adds that it is not a great day to be a batsman on this wicket.

New Zealand (Playing XI) - Tom Latham, Tom Blundell, Kane Williamson (C), Ross Taylor, Henry Nicholls, BJ Watling (WK), Colin de Grandhomme, Kyle Jamieson, Tim Southee, Neil Wagner (In place of Ajaz Patel), Trent Boult.

Virat Kohli, the Indian skipper, says that they would have bowled first as well but they are ready to do the difficult. Says that Umesh Yadav replaces Ishant Sharma, who is facing an injury and Ravindra Jadeja comes in for Ravichandran Ashwin. Goes onto say that they need to find ways to score on this wicket.

Kane Williamson, the New Zealand skipper, says that they are going to have a bowl first. Adds that the pitch has a greenish tinge on it and they give a chance for the pacers early on. States that Neil Wagner comes in for Ajaz Patel. Goes on to say that there will be bounce on this wicket.
Toss - Time for the spin of the coin. New Zealand have won the toss and they choose to bowl first.

Greetings! Welcome to our coverage of the second Test match between India and New Zealand. After being thrashed in the first Test, India would hope that they perform better and level the series. Ishant Sharma might miss out as his ankle injury resurfaced and that will be a big blow. They are set to retain Shaw as the second opener despite having a poor first Test. New Zealand, on the other hand, were brilliant with the ball at the Basin Reserve and to further bolster their bowling attack, Neil Wagner has been added to the squad. Who will he replace? Ajaz Patel or Kyle Jamieson? Toss and team updates in a while.

So, one session of play left. What will be India's approach? Will the 'intent' be there again, like it was in the first innings? We will soon find out. Will Shaw once again go for runs or will the Indians play safe in this final session? How the Kiwi pacers will fair? Will they trouble the Indians and strike early? Quite a lot of overs left for them to do so. Plenty of questions that need answers. We will have them soon. The final session will start at 1620 local. Join us for that.

Ravindra Jadeja is down for a quick chat. On the catch, he tells that he knew that the pull shot was coming and he was ready for it but didn't expect it to come so quickly but he managed to pluck it. Adds that he is happy with the performance. Credits the pacers and himself and says that everyone bowled well. Feels that they need to score runs now and then take 10 more wickets when they come to bowl.

After the 2-wicket over, the Indians once again failed to put the final nail in the coffin and allowed the tail to wag and score runs against them. Vihari spilled a chance when he put down Wagner on 3 and then Wagner added handy runs. Shami and Bumrah were excellent with the ball and ended up with 4 and 3 wickets respectively. Jadeja got two to his name along with two brilliant catches while Yadav was the one who got the first wicket in the morning session.

The umpires have taken TEA. Another excellent session for the visitors though. 93 runs have come in this one and India got 5 wickets in it. The session started with Bumrah picking two in one over to peg the Kiwis further back in the game. It looked like India was cruising towards a decent lead but de Grandhomme, Jamieson and Wagner made sure the Kiwis came closer to the Indian total. Jamieson once again missed out on his maiden Test half ton.

Finally, India get the last wicket to bundle the Kiwis out. They have managed to get a slender lead but that could've been a lot more. But the pair of Jamieson and Wagner added 51 runs to take the total closer to the Indian score.

On off, kept out off the back foot.
Length and outside off, de Grandhomme runs it down past point for a single.
On a good length and on off, de Grandhomme defends it off the front foot towards mid on.
Length ball on middle, de Grandhomme goes for the flick only to miss it and wear it on the pads.
Short of a length ball on middle, Jamieson flicks it towards mid-wicket and gets a run.
Length ball on off, Kyle blocks it off the back foot.
Full and on off, Jamieson drives it towards mid on and gets a single.
Flatter and on off, Kyle punches it off the back foot now.
Floated on off, Jamieson pushes it off the front foot towards the off side.
Flighted ball on  middle, Kyle pushes it to the left of the bowler who fields it in his followthrough.
Floated on off, pushed towards mid on.
Tossed up on off, pushed off the back foot.
Ravindra Jadeja is back on. 4-1-10-1 so far from him.
Length and outside off, Jamieson taps it to point and gets a run.
Length and on off, Kyle keeps it out off the back foot.
FOUR! That is driven with power. Jamieson showed in the first Test that he is no mug with the willow. Yadav goes full and Jamieson drives it crisply through covers for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Kyle drives it to covers now.
Full and on middle, Kyle drives it to mid on.
Length ball on off, Jamieson gets right behind the ball and keeps it out off the back foot.
Umesh Yadav to bowl for the first time in this session. 14-2-32-1 are his numbers so far.
Swing and a miss! Just ahead of a good length outside off, de Grandhomme drives away from his body but fails to connect.
Length ball on off, de Grandhomme looks to drive but gets an inside edge on the pads.
Three more! These are very valuable runs for the Kiwis. Full and on middle, Jamieson whips it through mid-wicket. Before the deep square leg fielder can come across, the batters take three.
Full and swinging in, Jamieson looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
A couple now! Length ball outside off, Jamieson hangs back and dabs it down to third man for a couple.
Good length ball on middle, pushed to mid on.

Length ball outside off, de Grandhomme runs this down towards third man and call for a couple and they get it. The umpire later signals it to be one short as the batter there  fails to lay his bat inside the crease properly while taking the run. So the batters get just one.
Length and outside off, de Grandhomme lets it be.
Length ball on middle, Colin misses his flick to wear it on the pads. There is an appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Another play and a miss. De Grandhomme now pokes at a length ball outside off only to get beaten.

Full and on off, Jamieson drives it straight down the ground. Jadeja from mid on flies to his left and makes an excellent stop. The batters though have taken off for the run. Jadeja fires the throw quickly at the non-striker's end but misses.
BEATEN! Wow! The ball is talking too much here. Shami bowls one on a length and gets it to move away and beats the outside edge of Jamieson's willow.
Outside off, Colin offers no shot to this one.
BEATEN! Full delivery outside off, de Grandhomme looks to drive but misses it.
Good length delivery on off, de Grandhomme blocks it off the back foot.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Colin looks to defend but misses it.
Full delivery outside off, de Grandhomme drives it through point. The batsmen get two runs.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, de Grandhomme looks to defend but misses it.
On a good length on off, Jamieson keeps it out.
Full delivery on middle, de Grandhomme flicks it through mid-wicket. Umesh Yadav runs from deep square leg and does well to stop it. The batsmen get three runs.
Length delivery outside off, de Grandhomme punches it to covers.

FOUR BYES! Another run which will go against Pant but he could've hardly done anything about it. A length ball outside off, de Grandhomme shoulders arms. The ball then after going past him, shapes away sharply. Pant throws himself to his right to collect but the ball evades him and goes to the fence behind.
Full and on the pads, de Grandhomme looks to flick but misses.
Bumper from Shami now. De Grandhomme does well to duck under it.
Outside off, Jamieson lets it go to the keeper.
Bouncer now but it is well over. Jamieson sits under it.
Good length ball around off, Jamieson keeps it out.
Full and on middle, Jamieson flicks but finds mid-wicket.
Shortish in length and on middle, Jamieson covers the line of the ball and keeps it out.
Play and a miss! Good length ball around off, Jamieson has to play at it. He pokes but the ball moves away and beats the outside edge. Bumrah is pretty close to getting another one.

Brilliant take from Pant. A length ball outside off, de Grandhomme lets it be. The ball keeps moving away after passing the batsman. Pant behind the wicket moves swiftly to his right and collects the ball with a tumble.

Angled into the pads on a good length, de Grandhomme fails to flick and gets hit on the pads. A loud appeal has been turned down. The third slip fielder catches the ball and appeals for a catch but the umpire is unmoved. They do not go for the review.
Goes full, invites de Grandhomme for the drive. De Grandhomme accepts it and drives away from his body to get beaten.
Shortish and around off, de Grandhomme blocks it off his back foot.
Good length ball around off, this time de Grandhomme gets behind the line to defend.
Ripper from Shami! It pitches around off on a good length and shapes away a hint. De Grandhomme pushes at it with hard hands but the ball beats his outside edge and goes behind.
Beaten! Another length ball outside off, Jamieson goes for the drive away from his body to get beaten.
Kyle Jamieson is in next.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Terrific from Bumrah and India. New Zealand are falling apart. A shortish length ball outside off, Southee pokes away from his body. A nothing shot to be honest. All he manages is a thin outside edge which goes to the keeper. Pant accepts it gleefully. No. 7 goes down with the hosts still 89 behind.
Good length ball around off, Southee looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Tim Southee joins de Grandhomme out in the middle.

OUT! CAUGHT! Screamer from Jadeja at point. Bumrah has his second. After bowling a few length balls, Bumrah dishes out a fuller ball outside off. Watling reaches out and looks to drive. He connects it well but it goes uppishly towards Jadeja at point. Jadeja there dives to his left and gobbles it superbly.
Good take from Pant. Good length ball outside off, Watling lets it be. The ball though keeps moving in as Pant does well  to move to his left and collect the ball.
Bouncer outside off, Watling lets it be.
Good length ball outside off, pushed towards point.
Bouncer on middle! De Grandhomme easily ducks under it.
Good length ball outside off, de Grandhomme shoulders arms at the very last moment.
FOUR! Driven firmly! Shami overpitches it just outside off, de Grandhomme slams it through mid off for a boundary. 150 up for the hosts.
Good length ball outside off, de Grandhomme plays a drive away from his body. The ball takes the inner part of his willow and goes towards the leg side.
Fuller and on off, de Grandhomme strokes it back to the bowler.
Mohammed Shami to bowl from the other end. 15-2-45-2 from him so far.
Wide outside off this time, Watling lets it be.
Good length ball around off, it is defended.
Slightly overpitched and de Grandhomme strokes it through covers. The ball goes towards the fence in the deep but the chasing fielder slides to pull it back. Three taken.
Outside off, left alone.
Excellent comeback from Bumrah. Pitches this way outside off and then makes it jag back into de Grandhomme sharply. De Grandhomme tries to defend but the ball goes past his inside edge to Pant.
FOUR! Flicked! Runs straightaway. Bumrah bowls the length ball on middle, de Grandhomme flicks it nicely towards deep square leg for a boundary.

We are back for the second session. The Indian players are out in the middle. BJ Watling and Colin de Grandhomme will resume their innings for New Zealand. Jasprit Bumrah will start the proceedings for the second session for India.
... Day 2, Session 2 ...

Right then! Still 100 behind and considerably two new batters in the middle, the Kiwis have a task in their hands. They will have to rebuild and try to get closer to the Indian total. The visitors though would like to get one quickly again in the next session and then they will have a chance to have a crack at the lower order of New Zealand. We are in for an exciting second session on our hands in this game. Join us at 1410 local.

It all started with Yadav removing Blundell in the 3rd over of the game. Bumrah got the massive wicket of Williamson to peg the Kiwis back. Then, the Indians kept chipping away with the wickets at regular intervals with all the bowlers getting a wicket to their name. Taylor had got himself in but fell to a very poor shot. Latham was the only one who gutted it out in the middle but got out leaving the ball after getting to his half ton.

79 runs and 5 wickets! What a session for India. They have turned the things around spectacularly in this game and they now head back into the game with a chance to take a lead as the Kiwis are still behind 100 than the Indian total.
In the channel outside off, Watling covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper. IT IS LUNCH ON DAY 2.
Good length ball around off, Watling gets behind the line of the ball to keep it out.

Another ball which has hit the pads but on a higher side as Shami makes it to come into de Grandhomme again from a good length. The ball this time hits his pad and goes towards point and they take a leg bye.
Good length ball around off, Shami nips it back into the right-hander. De Grandhomme looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Length ball outside off, de Grandhomme makes a leave.
FOUR! Nicely driven! Shami bowls a full ball outside off, de Grandhomme squeezes it between gully and point to bag a boundary.
Full and outside off, Watling strokes it well but straight to the man at mid off.
Fuller and around middle, Watling flicks it towards mid-wicket.

NOT OUT! Going over the stumps. Top, top decision, one has to say from the on-field umpire. A length ball angled into the batter, Watling looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pads. Bumrah makes a loud appeal. But the umpire disagrees. Bumrah this time convinces his skipper to go for the review. Time for the replays. Front foot is checked first. It is a legal ball. There is no inside edge which is confirmed by the Ultra Edge. Is it hitting the stumps? No, going over the stumps. India lose one of their reviews.

Huge LBW appeal has been taken upstairs by Kohli. Bumrah was convinced. Looked like there was an inside edge. They check with the front foot first. It is fine. No edge there, confirmed by Ultra Edge. Pitching in line too. Hitting the stumps? No! Review lost.
Shortish and outside off, Watling once again makes a leave.
Outside off, left alone.
Shortish length around off, it is blocked off the back foot.
On a good length on middle, de Grandhomme looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad. The bowler appeals for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
EDGY FOUR! On a good length on off, de Grandhomme looks to defend but gets an inside edge. It goes over the stumps towards fine leg for a boundary.
Colin de Grandhomme joins BJ Watling out in the middle.

OUT! CAUGHT! Yes, Kohli has his fingers under the ball. Excellent take from the Indian skipper. A good length ball around off, Nicholls looks to defend with hard hands. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards second slip. Kohli there lunges forward and gobbles the ball inches above the turf. Kohli starts celebrating straightaway. Nicholls though stands his ground and the umpires then get together to take it upstairs. The soft signal is out. They check the front foot first. It is fine. Now towards the business end. Looks like it's a clean catch as the replays show that Kohli has got his fingers around the ball and the third umpires says just that. India have got the fifth wicket.
Have India got another one? Kohli thinks so as he has taken a catch at second slip. The soft signal is out. That looks really close. Looks like Kohli has got his fingers under the ball.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Nicholls looks to defend but misses it.
Outside off, Nicholls does not bother to play at that.
On a good length and outside off, Nicholls shoulders arms to this one.

Huge appeal but it has been turned down. Length ball angled into the batter, Watling looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit high on the pads. Bumrah makes a loud appeal but the umpire is not impressed. The Indians do not go for the review once again and another good call from them as the Ball Tracker later rolls in and shows it to be going over the stumps.
Another length ball which is outside off, Watling lets it go to the keeper.
Shortish and around off, Watling keeps it out.
Length ball on middle, Nicholls clips it towards deep mid-wicket for a run.
Back of a length ball on middle, Nicholls pulls it towards deep square leg where Agarwal makes a tumbling stop to save two for his side.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
BJ Watling walks in next. Change in bowling too as Jasprit Bumrah returns.

OUT! Timber! The good morning for India is turning out to be a special one. Kohli has pumped up once again and he this time asks someone to keep their mouth shut. Brilliant from Shami. A length ball outside off, Latham thinks this will not come back in enough and shoulders arms. But to his bad luck, it sharply comes back in and pegs the off pole behind. 50 and out for Latham. Shami gets into the wickets too.
Good length ball on middle, worked towards mid-wicket.
Bouncer on middle, Latham ducks under it.
Another three! This time Nicholls runs it down to this length ball outside off through gully. Rahane once again chases it down and stops the ball just before the fence.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

FIFTY UP FOR TOM LATHAM. Fine innings so far. He has seen a few wickets fall in front of him but has kept his end intact. He has looked solid and will look to convert this into a big one. He gets to his 17th Test half ton by guiding this good length ball outside off through gully. Rahane from that positions chases it down and keeps it to three.
Fuller in length and on the stumps, Nicholls pushes it towards mid on.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Fuller and around off, Nicholls comes forward and blocks it out.
Length ball on middle, Latham works it down to fine leg for a run.
Shortish and around off, Latham goes on the back foot and keeps it out.
Yadav starts the spell with one down the leg side. Latham looks to flick but misses.
Umesh Yadav returns. 13-2-31-1 from him so far.
Another leave as Shami bowls this one wide outside off again.
Another ball which is wide outside off, Nicholls shoulders arms again.
Goes slightly fuller and makes the ball come back in from outside off, Nicholls watchfully pushes it back to the bowler.
Shortish in length and around off, Nicholls taps it towards covers off his back foot.
In the channel outside off, left alone.

FOUR! Clipped away nicely. That was a mere half pull/punch and it raced away. A shortish ball around off, Nicholls goes on the back foot and then looks to pull but then realizes that it is not on the perfect height to go for that shot. He then punches it and the ball races away to the vacant deep square leg fence. First boundary for Nicholls.
Full delivery on off, Nicholls drives it through mid off for a run.
Tossed up delivery on off, Nicholls comes down the track and blocks it.
Floated delivery on off, Latham comes down the track and plays it towards covers for a single.
Loopy delivery on off, Latham keeps it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Nicholls flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Latham flicks it through square leg for a run.
On a good length on off, Henry blocks it off the front foot.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Nicholls looks to defend but misses it.

FOUR BYES! It goes straight between Pant's legs! On a good length and outside off, Nicholls offers no shot to this one. It goes towards the keeper where Pant bends but the ball sneaks under him and it races towards the fence.
On a good length on off, Nicholls keeps it out.
Short delivery on leg, Nicholls pulls it through square leg. The batsmen get two runs.
Full delivery on off, Nicholls defends it off the front foot.
Another full ball on off, Latham comes forward and pushes it towards covers.
Full and around off, Latham keeps it out.
Henry Nicholls is in now.

OUT! CAUGHT! What a catch from Umesh Yadav and Taylor falls now. That was a poor shot from him. Taylor skips down the track and Jadeja spots that quickly and bowls it slightly short. Taylor is through to the shot but the ball turns away and takes the leading edge. The ball goes high in the air behind point. Yadav from point runs behind and takes a brilliant tumbling catch. He kept his eyes on the ball till then and swallowed it in the end. A needless shot from the experienced campaigner.
Floated delivery on middle, Taylor blocks it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Taylor defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Latham comes down the track and flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen get three runs.
Length delivery on off, Taylor taps it through point. The batsmen get two runs.

Huge appeal for caught behind but not given. Shami is convinced that there is an edge but not the others around him. A shortish length ball around off, it pitches and then shapes away from Taylor's defensive shot. It moves further away as Pant collects it to his right. Shami starts celebrating but not out says the umpire. He thinks that there is an edge but Kohli is not convinced and he does not go for the review. A good call as the Ultra Edge roll in and show that there was nothing as the ball went past the bat.
Good length delivery on off, Taylor looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes safely towards the slip region.
On a good length on middle, Taylor blocks it well.
Good length delivery on off, Taylor defends it off the back foot.
On a good length on middle, Taylor keeps it out.

DRINKS! An excellent morning hour for the Indians. Yadav and Bumrah are ones who have given them the breakthroughs. They have got the big fish, Kane Williamson cheaply as well. Another couple of wickets before the Lunch break will put them ahead in the game. Latham and Taylor would look to forge a stand and go to Lunch without any damage. Let's see how it pans out.
Loopy ball around off, Latham comes forward and defends it out.
Fuller and around off, Latham comes forward and keeps it out.
Leg slip comes in.
Full and around off, Latham looks to sweep but the ball bounces extra and hits the helmet.
Full and outside off, Latham pushes it towards covers.

Full and around off again, Taylor sweeps it nicely and it is racing to the fine leg fence but Shami who just finished his over runs to his right from deep square leg and stops the ball with his right foot. They take three but the umpire wants to check if it is a clean stop. It is, so top work from the pacer.
Fuller and quicker one around off and middle from Jadeja, Taylor comes forward and keeps it out.
Spin time as Ravindra Jadeja comes to bowl. Bowled just one over on Day 1. A slip and short leg placed.

FOUR! GLORIOUS! Held the pose for the cameras there, did Latham. Full and around off and middle, Latham just shows full face of the bat and punches it down the ground. No chance for anyone to get around the ball as it races away to the fence. 100 up for New Zealand.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Fuller and around off and middle, Taylor watches the ball till the end and then flicks it to fine leg for a run.
Shortish and on middle, Taylor stays on the back foot and keeps it out.

Good length ball around off and middle, Latham looks to work it on the leg side but the ball takes the inner half and towards square leg. They go for a quick run. Vihari quickly gets to the ball from mid-wicket and scores a direct hit at the non-striker's end with an underarm throw but Latham makes it in easily.
Outside off, left alone.
Another length ball around off, this time Latham waits for it and then taps it through gully. Rahane chases it down and stops it near the fence. Three taken.

WOW! How did that not hit the off pole? A length ball just outside off, it comes back in sharply. Latham thinks that he has the stumps covered but it is not the case. But to his luck, the ball just about misses the off pole and goes over the stumps.
Good length ball around off, Taylor tucks it towards mid-wicket and takes a run.
Fuller and outside off, Taylor watchfully pushes it towards covers.
Shortish and just outside off, Taylor lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Taylor forces it towards  point.
Third leave in a row as Shami once again delivers this ball outside off on a good length.
Gets closer to the off pole on a good length but not enough to make Latham play.
Outside off, left alone.
Slightly short and just outside off, Latham looks to cut but the ball takes the bottom edge and bounces behind the stumps.
Another ball from Shami which is outside off on a good length. Latham once again makes a leave.
Shami starts with a length ball outside off, Latham lets it go to the keeper.
Mohammed Shami to bowl for the first time on Day 2.
Another ball in the channel outside off, Taylor lets it go to the keeper.
Full and outside off, Taylor pushes it towards mid off.
In the channel outside off, left alone.

Excellent effort from Yadav! He has worked hard with the ball and now a very good effort in the field to save a couple of runs. Bumrah dishes out this length ball on the pads, Taylor glances it towards fine leg. Yadav from deep square leg runs to his right and stops the ball from going to the fence. A couple taken.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball on middle, Latham clips it towards deep mid-wicket for a run.
Length ball around off, Taylor pushes it towards mid on.
Fuller and just outside off, Taylor waits for the ball and drives it through point for a couple of runs.
Extra bounce there! Good length ball around off, Taylor hangs on the back foot to defend but the ball shoots up and then hits the handle of the bat and drops towards the leg side.
Back of a length ball on middle, Taylor blocks it off his back foot.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
FOUR! Short and outside off, Taylor is quickly on the back foot to slap it through point to get off the mark with a boundary.
A couple to end the over! Bumrah dishes out a full ball outside off, Latham drives it through covers and runs through a brace.
Another leave as this one is outside off on a length.
Good leave! Good length ball on middle and off, this one is shaping away. Latham spots that well, covers his stumps and offers no shot.
Shortish in length but way outside off, Latham lets it be.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller and around off, Latham covers the line and pushes it towards the bowler.
Good length around off, Taylor pushes it towards mid on.

A mild LBW appeal. Another length ball from Yadav which comes in with the angle. Taylor is late in getting his bat around the ball and he misses. But once again the Indians know that it is very high and hence the appeal dies down.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Taylor tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.
Shortish and around the pads, Latham works it fine down the leg side for a run.
Edgy! A length ball outside off, Latham looks to let it go very late and hence the ball takes the bottom edge and rolls through point for a couple of runs.
Length ball outside off, Taylor chases after it away from his body to get beaten. End of a successful and eventful over from Bumrah.

FOUR BYES! Pant could've done better. A length ball down the leg side, Taylor looks to flick but misses. Pant once again dives to his left but the ball once again evades him and goes to the fine leg fence.

Huge appeal for LBW but not given. It's all happening now. A length ball angled in, Taylor looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pads. The Indians make a loud appeal but the umpire turns it down. Bumrah tells the skipper that it was hit very high and so they do not think of the review.

FOUR BYES! That is harsh on the keeper because he could've done nothing about it. A bumper down the leg side which keeps coming in. Pant makes a valiant dive to his left but the ball still is miles away from his reach. It evades him and races away to the fence.
Around off, Taylor keeps it out.
Ross Taylor replaces Kane Williamson in the middle.

OUT! CAUGHT! Bumrah has finally got the reward of bowling consistent line and length. He is pumped up and so is the Indian skipper. And why wouldn't they be. This is the mighty wicket of Kane Williamson. Good length ball outside off, Williamson, so early in his innings lets these go to the keeper. But not this time as he pokes at it, only to get a faint nick behind. The ball goes behind and Pant moves to his right to gobble it comfortably. Two quick wickets for the visitors and they are right back in the game.
A leave to end the over as Yadav dishes it wide outside off.
Comes forward to this length ball and pushes it towards mid off.
Landed on a length on middle, Latham works it towards mid-wicket.
Outside off, Latham lets it be.
Edgy! Yadav once again lands the ball on a good length. This one shapes back in as Williamson comes forward to defend. It takes the inside edge and goes over the stumps to fine leg. A run taken.
In the channel outside off, Williamson covers his stumps and lets it be.
Another ripper from Bumrah. Shortish and just outside off, this one angles away as Latham comes forward looking to defend. He is once again lucky as the ball goes past the outside edge to the keeper.
Landed around off and middle, pushed to mid on.
Length ball around off, Williamson pushes it towards covers and takes a quick run.
Slightly shortish and just outside off, Williamson goes back and taps it towards the off side.
Wide outside off on a good length, Williamson is not bothered as he shoulders arms.

Brilliant bowling from Bumrah. He is just not able to get that edge. Bowls this one just around off on a length, the ball comes into Williamson who looks to defend but the ball beats his outside edge and goes to the keeper.
In the channel outside off, Latham lets it go to the keeper.
Beaten! It is a good length ball outside off, Latham chases after it but misses out.
Full ball on the pads, Williamson strokes it towards mid on for one to get off the mark.
Umesh Yadav was about to release the ball but Williamson moves away at the very last moment.
Skipper Kane Williamson walks in early on Day 2.

OUT! LBW! Hitting the stumps! Yadav strikes and draws first blood. Another good length ball angled into the batter from Blundell. He looks to defend it but misses to get hit on the pads. The Indians appeal and the umpire raises his finger after giving it some thought. Blundell goes to his partner and after having a brief chat, he takes the decision upstairs. The replays roll in and confirm that the front foot is fine. There's no bat either. It is pitching in line too. Hitting the stumps? Well, not really but it is clipping the top of the middle pole. So, umpire's call it is and Blundell has to depart early on Day 2. The Indians would sense an opportunity now.

Tom Blundell has been given OUT LBW but he has taken it upstairs. Looks really close. Let's see the replays. Front foot is fine. There is no bat involved, says the third umpire. It is pitching in line too. Is it hitting the stumps? Well, it is clipping the top of middle which is good enough for the decision to stay. New Zealand keep their review but Blundell has to go.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball coming into Blundell who tries flicking but misses to get struck on the pads.
Ripper to end the over! Just behind good length and around off, it pitches and shapes away as Latham tries to put bat on ball. Latham will feel he is a lucky man that he didn't edge that one.

Misfield and a couple of runs! Good length ball just outside off, Latham guides it towards gully with an angled bat. Rahane there dives to his left to field but ends up diving over the ball. A couple taken.
In the channel outside off, Latham lets it go to the keeper.
Another good length ball, this one is on the stumps line, Latham works it towards mid-wicket.
Good length ball around off, Latham comes forward and blunts it on the off side.
First runs on Day 2! Bumrah bowls a length ball angled into the right-hander. Blundell works it towards deep mid-wicket and takes a run.
Jasprit Bumrah to bowl from the other end. 7-1-19-0 from him on Day 1.
Good length ball on middle, Latham pushes it towards mid off. Good tight start from Yadav.
Bowls this one slightly fuller and just outside off. Latham is drawn into a front foot drive but the ball shapes away and beats the outside edge.
Landed around off and on middle, Latham keeps it out.
Sprays down the leg side on a slightly shortish length ball. Latham looks to glance but misses. Pant does well to dive to his right and collect the ball.
Good length ball around off and middle, Latham is solid in his defense.
Umesh starts with a length ball around off, Latham pushes it towards covers.

The Indian team is in a huddle near the ropes. They now disperse to their positions. Final words from skipper. The two Kiwi openers, Tom Latham and Tom Blundell stride out to the middle to resume their innings. Jasprit Bumrah is marking his run-up. A couple of jogs from him too but it is Umesh Yadav who will take the ball first up for the visitors. 2 slips in place. Here we go...

After an early loss, India did well to pull themselves back in the game with half tons from Shaw, Pujara and Vihari but they failed to convert their starts into big ones. The Kiwi bowlers even after being attacked, kept things tight and managed to get breakthroughs at regular intervals. A collapse came soon and the hosts were folded for 242. The Indian bowlers had 23 overs to make amends of their batters' poor show but they failed to get any wickets as Latham and Blundell dug in and looked solid in their 63-run unbeaten stand. Welcome to our coverage on Day 2 of the game. The  Indian bowlers will be hoping to turn this around in the morning session of the game while the hosts will be looking to get closer to the Indian total without much damage. Let's see which team takes the honors of winning the 2nd Day.
... Day 2, Session 1 ...

That's it from our coverage on Day 1. Day 2 promises to be an exciting day. The Indians will look to come back fresh in the morning session and take a few wickets. The Kiwis would love to see the two openers go on and score a big one and take their side closer to the Indian total. Join us for Day 2 on Sunday, 1st March 2020 at 1130 Local (2230 GMT, Previous day). Till then, it is goodbye from our side.

The Kiwis were relentless throughout the day. They kept coming hard at the Indians but Shaw's attacking approach meant that they could not get wickets at regular intervals. Southee then picked up a couple of prized scalps of Kohli and Rahane and post Tea, it was all about 3-innings old Kyle Jamieson who ripped the Indian middle order with a 5-fer. Boult and Wagner ended up with 2 and 1 wicket respectively.

Earlier in the day, after a rain delay, New Zealand invited India to bat first. India lost Agarwal early but Shaw looked in fine touch. He scored a brilliant half ton but perished in a poor fashion. His wicket brought a mini-collapse as India lost Kohli and Rahane quickly. Pujara though got himself in and added important 81 runs with Vihari. Both the batters reached their half tons but threw their wickets away. The score soon read 194/5 to 242/10.

Top stuff from Latham and Blundell means that the Kiwis head back to the pavilion with their noses ahead. The duo have already wiped out 63 runs from the 242 which the Indians have scored. They have played out 23 overs without much trouble and will return on Day 2 to make progress in this game. The Indian bowlers failed to produce the magic delivery in their 23 overs of the Kiwi batting and will have a hard task on their hands on Day 2.
Length ball on middle, Blundell keeps it out off the back foot to see of an eventful and fruitful day for New Zealand. That is STUMPS ON DAY 1!
On a shorter length and on off, Blundell hops inside the crease and keeps it out on the leg side. Last ball of the day coming up.
Short ball on off, Blundell evades it.
Short of a length ball on middle, Latham tucks it past the short leg fielder and towards mid-wicket for a single.
Another bouncer, this one for Latham. He is happy to sit under it.
Bouncer on middle first up and Blundell is up for the challenge. He pulls it with control towards deep square leg and before the man from fine leg can cut it off, they take three.
Shortish and around off, pushed towards point.
Length ball angled into the batter and Latham looks to leave it. The ball keeps coming in into the batter and goes over the stumps.
Beauty! Good length ball outside off, Latham pokes at it to get beaten.

Bouncer on middle, Blundell looks to pull but the ball takes the inner part of the bat and then hits the body. It lobs towards Shaw at short leg who has his eyes closed in an attempt of trying to stay away from the firing line of the pull shot. It goes between his legs and they steal a run.
On middle, this one is clipped behind square leg for an easy run.
Goes for the effort ball as bowls this back of a length on middle but Latham ducks it easily.
Jasprit Bumrah returns. 6-1-17-0 from him so far.
Tossed up on middle, Blundell keeps it out right under his eyes.
Floated on middle, Blundell tucks it to the leg side off the front foot.
Tossed up once again on off, Blundell defends by coming on the front foot.
Tossed up around off, Tom is happy to play the defensive prod.
Floated on off, Blundell keeps it out once again.
Fired in full and on middle, Blundell blocks it off the front foot.
Spin for the first time as Ravindra Jadeja comes into the attack. Maybe a couple of overs for him to roll his arms. Can he provide the breakthrough India is after?
Length ball on middle, Latham clips it towards mid-wicket.
Full and around off, blocked towards the off side.
FOUR! Class written all over! What a glorious shot. Shami overpitches a hint and Latham makes him pay for it. He comes forward and caresses it through mid off for the second boundary of the over.
Full and on middle, easily flicked to mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! 50 up for New Zealand! Just a mere punch and the ball races away to the fence. A length ball around off, Latham comes forward and strokes it past the diving cover fielder. He gets up and gives it a chase but comes second. Top start for the Kiwis.
Full and angling into the pads, Latham plays it behind square on the leg side for a run.
Length and on middle, Latham blocks it off the back foot towards the bowler.
Length ball outside off, Latham defends it to covers.
Length ball on off, Latham plays it back to the bowler.
Full and on the pads, Blundell flicks it to mid-wicket and gets to the other end.
Short ball on middle, Blundell transfers his weight on the back foot and then pulls it towards the deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Shami bends his back and bowls a back of a length ball on middle. Latham ducks under it easily.
Around off on a good length, Blundell tucks it behind square on the leg side for another easy run.
Neil Wagner is seen padded up inside the Kiwi dressing room. Interesting.
Shortish and around off, Blundell pushes it towards point.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Fuller and around off, blocked towards covers.
FOUR! Crunched! Short and wide outside off, Latham quickly transfers his weight on the back foot and flays it through point to bag a boundary.
Pacy bouncer from Umesh but Latham easily ducks under it.
Another leave as this one is way outside off on a good length.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, asking the batter to go for the drive but Latham says no and shoulders arms.
On the pads, flicked to mid-wicket.
Another play and a miss! Shami bowls in the channel outside off and Blundell pokes from within the crease only to get beaten on the outside edge.
BEATEN! Blundell loses his concentration there as he goes fishing outside off only to get beaten on the outside edge.
On a fuller length and around off, Blundell keeps it out towards point.
Full and angling into the pads, Blundell flicks it to mid-wicket now.
Fuller in length and on off, Blundell compactly defends it to point.
Length and on off, Blundell taps it to point.
Another ball on the hips, Latham looks to flick but once again fails to connect. It drops towards the leg side on the pitch. Before it can bounce back towards the stumps, Latham kicks it away.
Ouch! That will hurt. A bouncer on the body, Latham looks to defend but he misses. The ball hits his elbow and then drops on the pads.
On the pads, Blundell flicks it down to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Full and on the stumps, Blundell gets his bat down in time to keep it out.
Good length ball around off, blocked.
Short and outside off, Blundell pushes it towards mid off.
Another leave as Shami bowls this one on a length outside off.
Outside off, left alone.
Bouncer on middle! No problems for Latham in ducking under it.
Shortish and on middle, Blundell tucks it towards the leg side for a run.
Back of a length ball around off, Blundell swivels and looks to pull but the ball takes the bottom edge and drops onto the pitch.
Full and around off, Blundell comes forward and defends it out.
Length ball on middle, it is blocked towards mid-wicket.
Beaten! A length ball moving away after pitching. Latham looks to force it to the off side but misses.

Length ball on off, Blundell pushes it towards mid on and calls for a single. Latham obliges and the batters take a single. Bumrah from mid on swoops on the ball and has a shy at the bowler's end only to miss it. The ball instead hits the willow of Blundell and deflects. Blundell too is down on the ground as he falls while evading the throw from Bumrah.
OHH! That was close to shaving the off pole. Blundell makes the leave by covering his stumps. It is a length ball around off and coming in with the angle.
BEATEN! Length ball outside off, Blundell looks to punch it off the back foot only to get beaten on the outside edge.
Length ball way outside off, Blundell lets it be.
Umesh Yadav is back on! 4-1-8-0 so far from him.
Short ball down the leg side, Latham ducks under it.
Full and angled into the pads, Blundell flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller in length and on off, Latham pushes it to mid-wicket and hares for a quick single. In the end they get it.
Full and outside off, Latham watches the ball closely as he shoulders arms to it.
On a good length and outside off, Latham lets it be.
Length and outside off, Latham taps it to point.
Around off on a length, it is blocked.
Full and around off, Blundell flicks it nicely but finds mid on.
Shortish and around off, Blundell pushes it back to the bowler.
Full and around off and middle, this time Blundell strokes it to mid on.
Fuller and around off, Blundell is solid in his defense.
Good length ball around off, Blundell comes forward and looks to defend but gets an inside edge on his shoes.
Full and on the pads, flicked to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Shortish and around off, Blundell hops and keeps it out.
In the channel outside off, coming into the right-hander. Blundell lets it be.
On the pads, clipped to mid-wicket.
Shortish and just outside off, Blundell looks to force it on the off side off his back foot but misses.
Shami starts with a fuller ball just outside off, Blundell keeps it out.
Mohammed Shami is into the attack.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and angled into the pads, Latham flicks it to mid-wicket.
Loud shout for LBW but not given. Bumrah bowls one on a length and gets the ball to jag back into the batter, Latham looks to defend it but gets hit high on the pads.
EDGY FOUR! Bumrah lands one on a length and outside off, Latham plays it with soft hands and gets it in the gap between the slip cordon and gully. The ball races to the fence at third man.
Length and coming in with the angle, Latham is aware about his off pole as he makes a leave.
Length ball and swinging away from the batter, Latham makes a leave.
Slightly shorter and on middle, Blundell looks to pull but misses to get hit high on the pads.
FOUR! Overpitched and Blundell takes the full toll of it. He drives this full ball outside off through covers and fetches a boundary.
OHH! How often have we seen this in this innings? It is bowled on a length and outside off, Blundell covers his stumps and makes a leave.
Good length ball around off, it is blocked.

Did that carry to Kohli? No, it didn't. Just short. A length ball just outside off, Latham pokes at the ball with hard hands. The ball takes a thick outside edge and goes towards Kohli at second slip. He dives to his left and tries to catch but the ball lands just short. It hits his hands and goes towards short third man for a run.
Length ball on middle, Latham works it towards mid-wicket.
Slightly fuller but outside off again. Blundell lets it be. Once again the ball sharply moves in after going past the keeper.
FOUR! That's beautifully hit. Sweet timing on that. It is bowled fuller and around off, Blundell goes low and then drives it through covers for a boundary.
Fuller and on middle, Latham looks to flick but gets a leading edge towards cover for a run.
Length on off, Latham keeps it out.
Bouncer but off the target as it goes way down the leg side. Pant does well to pouch it with movement to his right.
Length ball on middle, played of the front foot and back to the bowler.

Just over the stumps! That was a brave leave! Yadav bowls an incoming ball which pitches just outside off and sharply moves into the batsman. Blundell covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.  It went just over the stumps.
Full ball just outside off, Blundell drives it back to the bowler.
Angled in on a slightly shortish length, Blundell tucks it towards square leg.
On the pads, Blundell tries to flick but misses.
Full and on middle, Blundell flicks but finds mid-wicket.
Another easy two as Yadav bowls a length ball on middle. Blundell clips it behind square leg and runs through for a brace.
On a length and on off, Latham keeps it out off the front foot.
Full and on off, blocked back to the bowler.
On the pads of Latham, he easily nudges it through square leg for a couple of runs.
Outside off on a length, Latham makes a leave.
Another good length ball around off, Latham once again forces it towards point.
Length ball around off, Latham pushes it towards point.
Slightly shorter and around middle, Blundell looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pads.
Landed on middle, Blundell clips it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller and around off, Blundell keeps it out.
Chases a length ball way outside off but fails to make any connection.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball on middle, Latham looks to work it on the leg side but the ball takes the outer half and goes towards point for a run.
Length ball around off, Blundell keeps it out.
FOUR! Blundell is off the mark in a streaky fashion. Good length ball around off, Blundell goes for the drive but the ball takes the inside edge and goes past the stumps to the fine leg fence.
Full and around off, pushed towards point.
Another ball outside off, Blundell covers his stumps and lets it be. The ball shapes back in a lot after going past the stumps and Pant does well to move to his left to collect.
Beaten! A length ball outside off, it comes in with the angle as Blundell tries to defend it off the back foot. He misses and the ball goes to keeper.
Fuller and around off, Blundell comes forward and keeps it out.
On a length and on off, Latham keeps it out off the front foot.
Length and outside off, Latham lets it go through to the keeper.

FOUR BYES! Short ball gone wrong. Yadav bangs one in but the line is down the leg side. Latham lifts his bat high and moves away from the line of the delivery. Pant behind the wickets leaps to his right but the ball evades him to go to the fine leg fence. Byes given.
Full and on leg, Blundell looks to flick it but gets it off the pads towards mid-wicket for a leg bye.
Another ball that is bowled outside off and Blundell is happy to let that be.
Length ball outside off, Blundell makes a leave to this away swinger.
Umesh Yadav to bowl from the other end.
Length ball on middle, worked towards mid-wicket.

Jaffa! What a beauty! Latham couldn't have done much. Just behind good length, it pitches around off and then shapes away as Latham looks to defend. It though beats the outside edge and goes to the keeper.
Good length ball on off, Latham pushes it towards point.
He is off the mark now! Too straight from Bumrah, Latham clips it behind square leg for a couple of runs.

Off the pads but the Kiwis are underway! Bumrah sprays on the pads of Latham who tries to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards fine leg and the batters cross for a couple of leg byes.
Bumrah starts with a good length ball angling away from the left-hander. Latham shoulders arms.

Right, just 132 runs to seal the series. Not a very big total but one should know that these can be defended. But for that to happen, India needs massive efforts from their bowlers. The pitch is offering support to the pacers and If India can strike early, we can have an interesting run chase on our hands. Join us for that in a while.

That didn't last too long, isn't it. Just 34 runs.  Not even one hour and India have been rolled over again by the Kiwis. The visitors needed efforts from Vihari and Pant but it didn't come. New Zealand needed just the two bowlers to finish the innings. Boult and Southee were too good for the Indians.

OUT! RUN OUT! Excellent awareness from Williamson. A shortish ball around middle, Jadeja taps it on the leg side. He takes a step forward and seeing that Bumrah responds and takes off. Jadeja though sees that Boult is charging at the ball, he sends Bumrah back. Boult collects the ball and fires the throw at the bowler's end but he misses. However, Williamson collects the throw and whips the bails quickly to find Bumrah short. The umpire raises his finger straightaway and does not think of checking it with the umpire upstairs. INDIA END WITH 124.
Sprays the length ball down the leg side. Jadeja goes for the flick but misses.
Shortish and around off and middle, Jadeja keeps it out off his back foot.

FOUR! The long on fielder is inside the ring and Jadeja pulls it over that fielder to bag another boundary. A length ball just outside off, Jadeja takes a step forward and lofts it over the mid on fielder for a boundary. The lead crosses 130 now.
Bouncer but it is down the leg side, Jadeja lets it go.

Call is for two and they will make it easily. A length ball around off, Jadeja looks to defend  but the ball takes the inner half and goes towards deep mid-wicket. Jadeja quickly calls for a couple and completes it.
Not a great ball to finish as Southee bowls a high full toss. Bumrah negotiates it with ease to get through the over.
Play and a miss again! Full and just outside off from Southee again, Bumrah once again fails to put bat on ball. One more delivery to survive.
Goes full and just outside off, Bumrah looks to get bat on ball but is beaten as the ball tails away.
FOUR! Tickled fine and 4 more vital runs. Southee sprays down the leg side and Bumrah just helps it down to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Full and just outside off, Bumrah lets it go to the keeper.
Survives the first ball as Southee bowls it wide outside off. An easy leave.
Tries to get a run and retain the strike as he goes to squeeze this fuller ball to deep cover but misses. Bumrah to face the next over.

SIX! Connects this time and sends it sailing over long on for maximum. Can he smack a few more to take India closer to 150? A length ball around off, Jadeja powers it over long on for a biggie. Vital six runs.
Swing and a miss! Full and just outside off, Jadeja goes for an all mighty slog but fails to connect. Had he connected, it would've landed in Australia.
Good length ball just outside off, Jadeja tries to push it towards the off side but misses.
Good length ball on middle, Jadeja keeps it out.
Length and outside off, Jadeja cuts it through point but denies the run.
Another leave as Southee bowls this one slightly fuller but outside off.
In the channel outside off, Bumrah lets it be.
Jasprit Bumrah is the last man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Shami holes out! Not sure if it was the time for this shot but he is Shami and he can do whatever he wants when he has the willow in his hand. He tries to slog this length ball on middle over deep mid-wicket but ends up miscuing it as the ball takes the inner half of the bat. Blundell at deep mid-wicket, well inside the ropes pouches it with ease. Interestingly, Jadeja did not cross and it will be Bumrah who will face the last two balls.

Did that carry to Watling? No, just short. A length ball outside off, Jadeja once again flirts with it. This time he gets an outside edge and the ball goes behind. Watling dives to his left and tries to catch but the ball falls just short. It goes behind the slip cordon and a run is taken.
Beaten! Way outside off on a length, Jadeja tries to play at it but misses.
Bouncer on middle, Shami pulls it with control to deep square leg.
Jadeja goes for the single on the last ball this time as Shami works this length ball on middle to find leg.
It's a defensive stroke! A full ball outside off, Shami pushes it to covers.

Full and on middle, Jadeja flicks it to mid-wicket and takes a run. A couple of balls for Shami to survive. Not sure if that will be on Shami's mind though as he loves to use the long handle. Let's see what he does.
Goes full this time, Jadeja pushes it to mid off.
In the channel outside off, Jadeja flirts with it to get beaten.

Bouncer aimed at the head of Jadeja. He takes the challenge on and goes for the pull but misses. Watling behind the wicket times his jump and collects the ball over his head. Certainly saved 4 important runs, did Watling for his side.
Full and just outside off, Shami strokes it to deep cover but Jadeja denies the single.
Short and around off, Pant helps it towards mid on with a gentle pull. He calls for a quick run.
Full and around off, Shami strokes it to mid off for a run.

Back of a length ball on middle, Shami wanted to go for the slog initially but the ball came back in and Shami in the end tried to fend it off the back foot but ended but getting a blow on his shoulders.
Length ball on the pads, Shami tries to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls to fine leg and the batters run a couple of leg byes.
Full and on middle, Jadeja flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a run. Southee won't mind bowling the next 5 balls to Shami. 100 up for India.
Beaten! Length ball just outside off, jags back in sharply as Shami tries to push at it.
Full and around off again, Shami flicks it uppishly towards mid on. The mid-wicket fielder gives it a chase and keeps it down to two.
Full and around off, Shami keeps it out.
Mohammed Shami is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another one bites the dust and the Kiwis have a perfect start to the morning. A good length ball outside off, just a hint of away movement. Pant looks to force it to the off side but ends up getting an outside edge. The ball goes behind and Watling accepts the catch easily. Pant's poor run with the bat continues. These are the times when India needs a knock from someone like Pant but he has thrown away another chance. India just 104 ahead.
Landed around off on a length, Pant pushes it back to the bowler.
Beaten! Boult bowls this just outside off on a length, Pant fiddles with the line to get beaten.
Lands this one around off and makes it to move away. Jadeja initially thinks of playing at it but at the last moment lets it go. End of a successful over from Southee.
Very full and around off, Jadeja pushes it to mid off.
Ravindra Jadeja is the new man in with the bat for the visitors.

OUT! Strangled down the leg side and India lose Vihari early. A top catch from Watling. This is not a wicket-taking delivery but New Zealand won't mind. It is a length ball down the leg side, Vihari tries to glance it fine but ends up getting a tickle behind. Watling moves to his left and dives to take a very good catch with both hands.
Outside off now, Vihari lets it be.
FOUR! First boundary of the morning! Southee bowls this length ball outside off, Vihari comes forward and drives it through point for a boundary.
Southee begins his second over with a length ball outside off, Vihari does not fiddle with it.
Bouncer to end the over. It is a good one too as it is on middle. Pant spots that early and ducks under it.
Full ball on middle, Pant flicks it nicely but de Grandhomme at mid-wicket makes a fine stop to his left.
Good length ball on the pads, tucked to mid-wicket.
In the channel outside off, moving away after pitching. Pant leaves it alone.
Length and on off, Pant works it to mid-wicket.
Boult starts with a bouncer outside off, Pant lets it be.
Trent Boult will partner with Time Southee from the other end.
Good leave to finish the over. Southee bowls this outside off on a good length and makes it come back in. Vihari covers his stumps and shoulders arms, trusting the bounce and line of the delivery.
Good length ball just outside off, Vihari moves to his off pole a hint and defends it out.
Another good length ball around off, Pant clips it to deep mid-wicket for a run. The lead for India is 100 now.
Good length ball around off, Pant comes forward and keeps it out.
In the channel outside off, Pant makes a leave.
Runs straightaway! Southee starts with a fuller ball on the pads. It swings in as Pant flicks it to fine leg for a couple of runs before the fielder from deep square leg can come to cut it across.

Time for the action! The Kiwi players are in a huddle with their skipper giving the final advice outside the ropes. The skipper now leads them to the middle. The two overnight Indian batters, Hanuma Vihari and Rishabh Pant follow them to resume their innings. It is quite overcast right now. So, we might get rain interruptions. Well, let's not think about that for the moment. Pant will take the strike first up. Tim Southee with the ball. 2 slips and a gully in place. Here we go...

97 runs ahead with 4 wickets in hand. If they take this lead closer to 180-200, we will have a match on our hands. They still have got Vihari and Pant in the middle who can score these runs for them. There is Jadeja too who can add valuable runs. What about the Kiwis? All it would take for them is just 4 good deliveries to bundle the Indians. They will look to do that as quickly as possible. Let's see if they can do so. Welcome to our coverage of Day 3 of this final Test.
... Day 3, Session 1 ...

So then, India have their backs against the wall. Just 97 ahead and 6 already back to the pavilion. Vihari and Pant will return on Day 3 and try to score as many as they can. They will also hope for runs from the lower order too. What about the hosts? They will look to quickly get the remaining wickets and then chase the smallest of targets. What does Day 3 hold? Join us on 2nd March 2020 at 1130 local (2230 GMT, Previous day) to find out. Till then, goodbye and take care.

The Kiwi bowlers were relentless in this innings. They kept coming hard at the Indian batters. They kept taking wickets at regular intervals. Boult started the procession and then he ended it too as he finished with a 3-fer. Wagner kept bowling short, Jamieson kept bowling short and troubled Rahane. Wagner eventually got the better of Rahane. De Grandhomme managed the mighty scalp of the Indian skipper.

After bundling the hosts 7 short of their first innings total, Indians came out to bat in the final session. Agarwal failed again. This time Shaw failed too. Kohli failed AGAIN. Pujara battled. He defended, and ducked. Rahane who joined him after the wicket of Kohli had other thoughts. He wanted to take the short ball challenge on. He got hit on the helmet, took a few on the gloves and then ended up dragging one onto the stumps. Then Pujara fell to a peach from Boult. And now, India are in a spot of bother.

WOW! What a day of Test cricket! 86.1 overs, 262 runs and 16 wickets. Who is on top? Clearly New Zealand. They have picked up 6 Indian wickets with India's lead still under 100. Sensational bowling in the final session from New Zealand bowlers have put India on the back foot.
Shortish and around off from Boult. Vihari comes forward and then goes back to keep it out.
Full and around off, Vihari  comes forward and keeps it out. Last ball of the day coming up.
Delivers a length ball outside off from wide off the crease. Vihari has his stumps covered as he lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length ball on middle, Vihari keeps it out.
Full and on middle, Pant flicks it towards mid on and takes a quick run.
Rishabh Pant is in now.

OUT! BOWLED 'EM! Too good for a tailender there. Boult is just too good with the cherry in his hand. He comes round the wicket and angles it into the off pole, Yadav who is camping on the back foot is found wanting too much on this ball. In the end he decides to flick it to the leg side but is late in doing so. The ball sneaks between the bat and pad to crash into the off pole. India's sorry tale with the bat continues. New Zealand are once again dictating the terms here.
Full and on the pads, Vihari flicks it to the leg side.
Shortish and around middle, Vihari keeps it out.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off this time. Vihari is on the toes quickly and slams it through point for a boundary.
Bouncer now! Vihari sits under it.
On the pads, worked towards the leg side.
Shortish and around middle, Vihari keeps it out.
Shortish and around off, Umesh defends it off his back foot.
Fuller and around off, Yadav keeps it out.
Bouncer down the leg side, Yadav looks to pull but misses.
Full and angling into the pads, Vihari tucks it to square leg for a single.
Good length ball on off, Vihari keeps it out.
Hanuma Vihari is the new man in.

OUT! Goes through the defense of the best defensive Indian batsman! What a brilliant piece of bowling from Boult. He angles a length ball from outside off into the right-hander. Pujara tries to defend but the incoming ball sneaks through his defense and disturbs the woodwork behind. This is a huge blow for India. Pujara's fighting effort comes to an end. Wonder if he could've done anything to this peach from Boult.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.

Full toss on middle, Pujara whips it towards deep mid-wicket. The ball is racing towards the fence. Boult from fine leg runs till deep mid-wicket and pulls the ball before it can reach the fence. Total commitment from the speedster.
In the channel outside off, Pujara ducks under it.
Short ball down the leg side, Pujara ducks and lets it be.
Length ball on leg, Yadav pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Full and around off, Pujara drives it straight down the ground through mid off. But lack of timing means the ball fails to cross the fence at long off. Three is what the batters get.
Full and swinging in, Yadav looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. A mild appeal from Boult but he knows there was an inside edge.
Bouncer for Yadav. It is on middle but Yadav ducks.
Length ball around off, Yadav pushes it towards point.
On the pads on a good length, Pujara looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls to deep square leg and they change ends taking a leg bye.
Bouncer angled in from outside off, Pujara sways away from the line of the ball.
Full ball on off, pushed back to the bouncer.
Trent Boult returns. 6-2-10-1 from him so far.
Shorter in length and around off, Yadav keeps it out.
Good length ball around off, blocked.
FOUR LEG BYES! Wagner welcomes  Yadav with a bouncer on leg, Yadav misses his flick and gets it off his thigh pad toward the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Umesh Yadav comes in as a night watchman now.

OUT! DRAGGED ON! Wagner roars, it's a mighty one as he says, 'COME ON'. Rahane's struggle is over. He has been put off by the bouncers so all he is expecting is another bouncer. This one from Wagner does not rise much but Rahane has already moved in the position of playing a pull. He realizes the pull short is not on so he tries to help it to fine leg but ends up cannoning the ball onto the stumps off his pads. Brilliant stuff from Wagner. He kept bowling the bouncers and has finally got the reward.
Full and on off, Pujara drives it towards Williamson at covers who parries it towards towards mid off. The batsmen cross ends.

Another sharp bouncer, Rahane fends it off his gloves.

Another one but this one is down the leg side. Rahane watches it go past him.
Bouncer again! Rahane ducks.
Barrage of the bouncers continue. But this one is for Pujara. You know what he does, well, most of the times, sits under it.
